00:41:20.650 --> 00:41:22.900
AUDIENCE: I'm curious what
your thoughts are about

00:41:22.900 --> 00:41:24.370
transitioning between visionary

00:41:24.370 --> 00:41:25.700
and analytical companies.

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:28.400
Either you try to do it, or
you're forced to do it.

00:41:28.400 --> 00:41:30.800
Like in the case of Apple, they
lose a visionary leader,

00:41:30.800 --> 00:41:33.190
and maybe there's nobody
there to replace them.

00:41:33.190 --> 00:41:35.330
MICHAEL MACE: Yes, so
transitioning between a

00:41:35.330 --> 00:41:36.720
visionary and an analytical
company.

00:41:36.720 --> 00:41:38.060
Really, really hard to do.

00:41:38.060 --> 00:41:40.100
Usually, it fails.

00:41:40.100 --> 00:41:42.030
Apple tried to prepare
really hard.

00:41:42.030 --> 00:41:44.030
And it's not clear, by the way,
that Apple has decided

00:41:44.030 --> 00:41:45.890
that it wants to be an
analytical company.

00:41:45.890 --> 00:41:49.910
They did a huge amount of
training on how did Steve

00:41:49.910 --> 00:41:52.040
think, and what would Steve do,
and that sort of stuff,

00:41:52.040 --> 00:41:53.760
not in the sense that they
wanted people to literally

00:41:53.760 --> 00:41:56.800
say, well, what decision
would Steve have made?

00:41:56.800 --> 00:41:58.810
But it's kind of like, what
were the mental habits?

00:41:58.810 --> 00:42:00.230
How did he look at the world?

00:42:00.230 --> 00:42:02.950
And the interesting question
about Apple is, are they going

00:42:02.950 --> 00:42:05.630
to be able to institutionalize
that visionary function?

00:42:05.630 --> 00:42:08.610
Do they have some people in
house who can do that stuff?

00:42:08.610 --> 00:42:11.380
Or do they need to convert
themselves over to analytical?

00:42:11.380 --> 00:42:14.000
The problem with trying to
convert to analytical is

00:42:14.000 --> 00:42:16.480
almost all of your business
processes need to be changed.

00:42:16.480 --> 00:42:18.170
If you're going to be
analytical, you need a lot

00:42:18.170 --> 00:42:19.070
more process inside.

00:42:19.070 --> 00:42:21.810
You need different sorts of
managers who can do analytical

00:42:21.810 --> 00:42:23.830
thinking, as opposed to the
people you've hired to

00:42:23.830 --> 00:42:26.420
implement your vision, who are
very tell me what to do, let

00:42:26.420 --> 00:42:27.780
me just carry it out.

00:42:27.780 --> 00:42:30.090
You need people who can kind
of think about stuff more.

00:42:30.090 --> 00:42:32.720
So it is a really, really
hard thing to do.

00:42:32.720 --> 00:42:35.230
And usually, what happens
is the companies fail.

00:42:35.230 --> 00:42:39.010
If they've got enough runway,
if they've got enough money,

00:42:39.010 --> 00:42:40.670
then it's easier to make that
transition, as they've got

00:42:40.670 --> 00:42:42.760
more time, and Apple certainly
has a ton of money.

00:42:42.760 --> 00:42:44.310
So it'll be interesting
to see how it goes.

00:42:44.310 --> 00:42:46.080
But there's no exact playbook
for how to do it.

00:42:46.080 --> 00:42:48.010
It's a great question,
but there's no single

00:42:48.010 --> 00:42:49.710
way to make it happen.

00:42:49.710 --> 00:42:52.660
AUDIENCE: Basically, principles
discussed here, the

00:42:52.660 --> 00:42:56.810
propensities of two types of
thinking, I think also maybe

00:42:56.810 --> 00:42:59.010
apply to the individual level.

00:42:59.010 --> 00:42:59.410
MICHAEL MACE: Yes.

00:42:59.410 --> 00:43:02.910
AUDIENCE: So people tend to have
this intuitive thinking

00:43:02.910 --> 00:43:04.220
or analytical.

00:43:04.220 --> 00:43:07.880
So can you comment on those kind
of things based on your

00:43:07.880 --> 00:43:08.985
[INAUDIBLE]?

00:43:08.985 --> 00:43:09.890
MICHAEL MACE: Yeah.

00:43:09.890 --> 00:43:13.520
So individuals who are either
intuitive or analytical in the

00:43:13.520 --> 00:43:14.600
way they approach things--
which is

00:43:14.600 --> 00:43:16.240
completely true, they exist--

00:43:16.240 --> 00:43:19.220
the big thing is, make sure that
you are at a company that

00:43:19.220 --> 00:43:22.740
respects whatever your style is,
and make sure you're in a

00:43:22.740 --> 00:43:24.550
role that rewards that stuff.

00:43:24.550 --> 00:43:27.950
So for instance, if you're a
really analytical thinker, and

00:43:27.950 --> 00:43:31.680
you're just doing analysis, you
probably actually don't

00:43:31.680 --> 00:43:34.670
want to try to do competitive
analysis, because usually, you

00:43:34.670 --> 00:43:37.170
have limited data available on
competitors, and you have to

00:43:37.170 --> 00:43:39.390
form a lot of conjectures about,
OK, based on the little

00:43:39.390 --> 00:43:40.830
things that I know, here's
what they're

00:43:40.830 --> 00:43:42.140
probably going to do.

00:43:42.140 --> 00:43:44.080
However, if you're analytical,
you could be a really, really

00:43:44.080 --> 00:43:46.670
good market researcher, because
so much of that is

00:43:46.670 --> 00:43:47.750
dealing with data.

00:43:47.750 --> 00:43:51.870
So it's find a job that
will use your

00:43:51.870 --> 00:43:53.660
strengths, number one.

00:43:53.660 --> 00:43:55.310
And number two, work in a
company-- it doesn't have to

00:43:55.310 --> 00:43:57.190
be, oh, I'm a visionary,
therefore, I want to be in a

00:43:57.190 --> 00:43:57.910
visionary company.

00:43:57.910 --> 00:44:00.720
In fact, if you're a visionary,
and you work in a

00:44:00.720 --> 00:44:03.430
visionary company, that can be
very, very uncomfortable,

00:44:03.430 --> 00:44:05.000
because your vision may
not be the same as the

00:44:05.000 --> 00:44:06.150
vision of the CEO.

00:44:06.150 --> 00:44:09.720
You'll just get your butt fired
really, really fast.

00:44:09.720 --> 00:44:12.910
But find a situation where the
company will let you do what's

00:44:12.910 --> 00:44:15.570
your special added value, will
respect it, and will let you

00:44:15.570 --> 00:44:17.360
go optimize the thing
that you're best at.

00:44:17.360 --> 00:44:19.000
That's the big thing.

00:44:19.000 --> 00:44:20.390
And it's not a particular
job title.

00:44:20.390 --> 00:44:22.570
It's do your managers understand
what you do?

00:44:22.570 --> 00:44:24.610
Do you understand what you're
good at so that you can

00:44:24.610 --> 00:44:25.850
describe that to them?

00:44:25.850 --> 00:44:28.362
It's back to my general rule for
all career management in

00:44:28.362 --> 00:44:29.090
the Valley.

00:44:29.090 --> 00:44:30.530
Get hired for the
right reason.

00:44:30.530 --> 00:44:33.140
Get hired because they really
understood you, not because

00:44:33.140 --> 00:44:35.080
you made a good pitch
for a job.

