00:44:53.970 --> 00:44:56.430
And I'll give you my take, which
I don't expect all of

00:44:56.430 --> 00:44:57.350
you to agree with.

00:44:57.350 --> 00:45:01.090
But this is me on the outside
having watched Google a lot is

00:45:01.090 --> 00:45:05.570
that, although a lot of people
want to always say that Google

00:45:05.570 --> 00:45:08.280
is a visionary company, because
it did so much to

00:45:08.280 --> 00:45:11.980
found the internet, and there
are projects that you guys are

00:45:11.980 --> 00:45:13.870
doing that are definitely
visionary-- like I'd say the

00:45:13.870 --> 00:45:17.490
self driving car and Google
Glass and things like that are

00:45:17.490 --> 00:45:20.680
pretty much visionary things,
the core of the company

00:45:20.680 --> 00:45:23.360
behaves like an analytical
company.

00:45:23.360 --> 00:45:24.980
That is the process
that you guys do.

00:45:24.980 --> 00:45:27.740
Your emphasis on data and
quantification, on

00:45:27.740 --> 00:45:32.150
understanding things, that's all
normal behavior for when

00:45:32.150 --> 00:45:34.530
engineers are running the show,
because engineers are

00:45:34.530 --> 00:45:36.090
trained in the scientific
method.

00:45:36.090 --> 00:45:38.770
Scientific method says you run
a series of experiments that

00:45:38.770 --> 00:45:40.160
you then evaluate rigorously.

00:45:40.160 --> 00:45:42.680
You can have intuition, but
intuition that hasn't been

00:45:42.680 --> 00:45:44.930
tested through experiment
is distrusted by

00:45:44.930 --> 00:45:46.420
the scientific method.

00:45:46.420 --> 00:45:48.500
And you see that sort
of behavior

00:45:48.500 --> 00:45:49.690
repeatedly within Google.

00:45:49.690 --> 00:45:53.500
I'll give you one little tell
that me as a competitive guy

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:55.480
looks at a lot is just how
do companies talk about

00:45:55.480 --> 00:45:56.630
themselves?

00:45:56.630 --> 00:46:00.780
There's a phrase that the
internet companies developed a

00:46:00.780 --> 00:46:04.110
long time ago, which is, if you
can measure it, you can

00:46:04.110 --> 00:46:05.310
improve it.

00:46:05.310 --> 00:46:07.770
That was the whole rationale
behind analytics and all the

00:46:07.770 --> 00:46:09.430
other stuff that we do, looking
at your server logs,

00:46:09.430 --> 00:46:10.350
all that other stuff.

00:46:10.350 --> 00:46:13.060
If you can measure it, you can
improve it, which makes

00:46:13.060 --> 00:46:13.680
perfect sense.

00:46:13.680 --> 00:46:15.480
I do not argue with it at all.

00:46:15.480 --> 00:46:18.470
Several times over the last
couple of years, I've heard

00:46:18.470 --> 00:46:21.880
Google executives in public
forums flip it around.

00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:23.330
So they don't say it that way.

00:46:23.330 --> 00:46:26.360
What they say is, if you
can't measure it, you

00:46:26.360 --> 00:46:28.540
can't improve it.

00:46:28.540 --> 00:46:30.070
And if you want separately,
I'll go show you the

00:46:30.070 --> 00:46:32.750
references to when
that's been said.

00:46:32.750 --> 00:46:35.230
If you can't measure it,
you can't improve it.

00:46:35.230 --> 00:46:38.590
Now, what that says mentally
is, that which we cannot

00:46:38.590 --> 00:46:41.370
measure is irrelevant, and
therefore, should not be

00:46:41.370 --> 00:46:42.870
considered.

00:46:42.870 --> 00:46:46.120
If you had said that to Steve
Jobs, what would he have done

00:46:46.120 --> 00:46:48.740
to you, if you'd been one
of his employees?

00:46:48.740 --> 00:46:51.190
So that's how a visionary
would view

00:46:51.190 --> 00:46:52.820
that sort of statement.

00:46:52.820 --> 00:46:55.180
And yet, Google executives
repeatedly say that in public,

00:46:55.180 --> 00:46:58.050
with nobody contradicting it,
nobody noticing anything about

00:46:58.050 --> 00:46:59.640
it, nobody saying, well,
that seems odd, or

00:46:59.640 --> 00:47:00.430
anything like that.

00:47:00.430 --> 00:47:05.170
It is a reflection of the way
this company's behaviors and

00:47:05.170 --> 00:47:07.240
thinking tend to be formatted.

00:47:07.240 --> 00:47:10.680
Now, no companies is ever 100%
visionary or 100% analytical,

00:47:10.680 --> 00:47:12.170
and you can't try to be in
the middle, by the way.

00:47:12.170 --> 00:47:13.820
That's the worst, because you
never get anything done.

00:47:13.820 --> 00:47:16.170
There's nothing wrong with being
an analytical company.

00:47:16.170 --> 00:47:19.800
But my long answer to your short
question was, to me,

00:47:19.800 --> 00:47:23.670
Google looks like an analytical
company that does

00:47:23.670 --> 00:47:25.190
some experiments with visionary

00:47:25.190 --> 00:47:26.660
projects on the side.

00:47:26.660 --> 00:47:27.805
That's how it parses to me.

